State MSM Profile: Alaska

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Alaska

An estimated 5,074 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Alaska in 2013, representing 0.1% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 278,464 adult men of Alaska, 1.8% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Alaska resided in counties within medium or small metropolitan areas (69.4%). No MSM in Alaska resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Alaska, 2013

MSM in Alaska Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Alaska, Anchorage Municipality had the largest population of MSM at 2,541, representing 50.1% of all MSM in the state. Kodiak Island Borough had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Alaska at 4.4%. This was greater than the percentage for Alaska as a whole, which was 1.8% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Alaska Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Anchorage Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Anchorage MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Alaska at 2,939, or 57.9% of all MSM in the state. Of the 145,163 adult men in Anchorage, an estimated 2.0% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Fairbanks Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Fairbanks MSA had a population of 584 MSM, or 11.5% of all MSM in Alaska. Of the 39,373 adult men in Fairbanks, an estimated 1.5% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
